The paper deals with semantic image segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed architecture involves the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which are a popular tool in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the challenges of pixel-wise labelling and the need for global information, which are topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on the PASCAL VOC 2012 benchmark, which is a dataset commonly used in natural language processing and computer vision (cs.CL).
